(((((((The deception of the whole world by Satan/Anti-Christ/False Prophet. You will not be deceived if I and the Holy Spirit have something to say and do about it. If my family and friends and acquaintances care about their eternal soul, please read on and tell others.)))))))


**I am the Watcher on the Wall**


***The revelation of Jesus Christ, which God gave unto him, to show unto his servants things which must shortly come to pass; and he sent and signified it by this angel unto his servant John. (Revelation 1:1).


***Blessed is he that readeth, and they that hear the words of this prophecy, and keep those things which are written therein: for the time is at hand. (Revelation 1:3).


***But if the watchman see the sword come, and blow not the trumpet, and the people be not warned; if the sword come, and take any person from among them, he is taken away in his iniquity; but his blood will I require at the watchman’s hand. (Ezekiel 33:6).


***Even him, (Anti-Christ), whose coming is after the working of Satan with all power and signs and lying wonders, and with all deceivableness of unrighteousness in them that perish, (The preaching of the Cross is foolishness to those who are perishing but to us who are saved it is the power of God. 1 Corinthians 1:18), because they received not the love of the truth, that they might be saved. (People who refuse to repent of their sins and keep Jesus commandments). And for this cause God shall send them strong delusion, that they should believe a lie. That they all might be damned who believed not the truth, but had pleasure in unrighteousness. (2
Thessalonians 2:9-12). (So God is going to send the whole world, of the people that are perishing ,a strong delusion to accept world peace and a one world religion and the agenda of the Anti-Christ because, people wanted to live in unrighteousness, according to the bible).


***And he causeth all, both small and great, rich and poor, free and bond, to receive a mark (IN) their right hand, or (IN) their foreheads: And that no man might buy or sell, save he that had the mark, or the name of the beast, or the number of his name. (Revelation 13:16-17).
***And in those days shall men seek death, and shall not find it; and shall desire to die, and death shall flee from them. (Revelation 9:6).


***And the third angel followed them, saying with a loud voice, if any man worship the beast and his image, and receive his mark in his forehead, or in his hand, the same shall drink of the wine of the wrath of God, which is poured out without mixture into the cup of his indignation; and he shall be tormented with fire and brimstone in the presence of the Holy angels, and in the presence of the Lamb, (And the lamb is Jesus). And the smoke of their torment ascendeth up forever and ever: and they have no rest day nor night, who worship the beast and his image, and whosoever recieveth the mark of his name. Here is the patience of the saints: here are they that keep the commandments of God and the faith of Jesus. (Revelation 14:9-12).


***(God tells the seven angels to pour the bowls of his wrath on the earth): So the first went and poured out his bowl upon the earth, and a foul and loathsome sore came upon the men who had the mark of the beast and those who worshiped his image. (Revelation 16:2).


***I saw thrones on which were seated those who had been given authority to judge. And I saw the souls of those who had been beheaded because of their testimony about Jesus and because of the word of God. They had not worshiped the beast or its image and had not received its mark on their foreheads or their hands. They came to life and reigned with Christ a thousand years. (Revelation 20:4).


***And they overcame him, (Satan), by the blood of the Lamb, and by the word of their testimony; and they loved not their lives unto the death. (Revelation 12:11).


***Precious in the sight of the LORD is the death of his saints. (Psalms 116:15).


***And I saw an angel come down from heaven, having the key of the bottomless pit and a great chain in his hand. And he laid hold on the dragon, that old serpent, which is the Devil, and Satan, and bound him a thousand years, And cast him into the bottomless pit, and shut him up, and set a seal upon him, that he should deceive the nations no more, till the thousand years should be fulfilled: and after that he must be loosed a little season. (Revelation 20:1-3).


***And the beast was captured, and with him the false prophet that wrought miracles before him, with which he deceived them that had received the mark of the beast, and them that worshiped his image. These both were cast alive into a lake of fire burning with brimstone. (Revelation 19:20).
(This will happen when the King of Kings and Lord of Lords Jesus comes back with his mighty angels and his saints to rage war. Lol, the fallen angels and those who follow them, don’t even have a chance).


***And the remnant were slain with the sword of him, (Jesus), that sat upon the horse, which sword proceeded out of his mouth, and all the fowls were filled with their flesh. (Revelation 19:21).


***And the devil that deceived them was cast into the lake of fire and brimstone, where the beast and the false prophet are, and shall be tormented day and night forever and ever. (Revelation 20:10).


(See Satan knows his fate. And those who follow him WILL experience the same for eternity)………
